    • Enum Constant Detail

      • RECTANGLE

        public static final VisualShape.VisualShapeType RECTANGLE
        Rectangle bounding box. Valid value format is: "topLeftX,topLeftY,bottomRightX,bottomRightY", where all values are positive integers detonating pixel positions in the photo.

      • TRIANGLE

        public static final VisualShape.VisualShapeType TRIANGLE
        Triangle bounding area. Valid value format is: "topX,topY,bottomLeftX,bottomLeftY,bottomRightX,bottomRightY", where all values are positive integers detonating pixel positions in the photo.

      • CIRCLE

        public static final VisualShape.VisualShapeType CIRCLE
        Cricle bounding area. Valid value format is: "centerX,centerY,radius", where all values are positive integers detonating pixel positions in the photo.

      • POLYGON

        public static final VisualShape.VisualShapeType POLYGON
        Polygon bounding area. Valid value format is: "1X,1Y,2X,2Y...nX,nY", where all values are positive integers detonating pixel positions in the photo. There should be at least 3 coordinates for a valid polygon, though it is recommended to use TRIANGLE and RECTANGLE for simpler objects.
